- VSCode Version:1.3.1
- OS Version: Windows 10 1511

var filepath = 'C:\Users\abhi\documents\abc.txt";  // abc does not exist
var fileUri = vscode.Uri.parse('untitled:' + filePath);
vscode.workspace.openTextDocument(fileURI).then(doc => {
            vscode.window.showTextDocument(doc);
});

the above code fails as openTextDocument throws with **Cannot read property 'length' of undefined** .

But if I change the uri statement to 
var fileUri = vscode.Uri.parse('untitled:' + path.sep + path.sep + filePath);  // path = require('path');
Then untitled file opens fine. but the name of file is **\C:\Users\abhi\documents\abc.txt**

I am assuming there is a bug here. according to documentation first method should have worked.
